# Design system

Path-scoped rule. Loads when working in any UI file.

This rule has two layers. **Tokens are normative.** `<!-- PARAMETERIZE: token_file_path -->` is the source of truth for every color, spacing, radius, shadow, and motion value. Product UI must resolve through a CSS custom property, never a literal. **This rule is non-normative rationale.** It carries the design judgment that lives outside the codebase and does not duplicate token values. If the two ever conflict, the CSS file wins.

**Hard rule:** no hardcoded hex values anywhere in product UI. <!-- OPTIONAL: linter_line --> The `<!-- PARAMETERIZE: token_linter_command -->` linter enforces this and is wired into `npm run check`.

## Foundations

- **Typography:** <!-- PARAMETERIZE: typography_rules -->.
- **Motion:** <!-- PARAMETERIZE: motion_tokens -->. No bounce, no spring.
<!-- OPTIONAL: no_tailwind_ban -->
- **No Tailwind. No shadcn.** Style everything via the design system CSS.
- **Icons:** <!-- PARAMETERIZE: icon_set --> only.

